Package: graphfast
Type: Package
Title: Fast Graph Connectivity Analysis Using C++
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Kyle", "Haynes", email = "kyle@kylehaynes.com.au",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: High-performance graph connectivity analysis for large-scale datasets.
    Uses optimized C++ algorithms via Rcpp to handle hundreds of millions of
    node pairs efficiently. Provides functions for finding connected components,
    shortest paths, connectivity queries, and graph-based entity resolution
    with minimal memory footprint.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: 
    R (>= 3.5.0)
Imports: 
    Rcpp (>= 1.0.0),
    methods,
    data.table,
    fastmatch
LinkingTo:
    Rcpp
RoxygenNote: 7.3.2
Suggests:
    testthat (>= 3.0.0),
    knitr,
    rmarkdown,
    microbenchmark
VignetteBuilder: knitr
